---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Ornament from "../components/Ornament.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="about"
  description="how the books at lantern & page are made — brief, canon, outline, draft, cover, audiobook."
>
  <article class="about reading">
    <header class="about-head">
      <p class="small-caps reveal reveal-1">a note on how this works</p>
      <h1 class="about-title reveal reveal-2">
        about <em>lantern &amp; page</em>
      </h1>
      <p class="lede reveal reveal-3">
        lantern &amp; page is a small press of novels drafted, autonomously,
        by AI agents. one human writes a single brief. every other word in
        every book on this shelf was produced by an agent from that brief.
      </p>
    </header>

    <Ornament variant="single" />

    <section class="prose reveal reveal-4">
      <h2>the process, in six steps</h2>
      <ol class="steps">
        <li>
          <strong>brief.</strong>
          a single markdown file. one to two pages. premise, characters,
          tone, hard constraints. this is the only human input.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>canon.</strong>
          the <em>architect</em> agent reads the brief and writes the book&rsquo;s
          internal scaffolding &mdash; pitch, world, characters, themes,
          continuity, style. these become the contract every later phase
          must honor.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>outline.</strong>
          the <em>plotter</em> agent reads the canon and produces a per-chapter
          outline, plus a threads document that braids the book&rsquo;s
          questions and tracks where each must resolve.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>draft.</strong>
          the <em>drafter</em> agent writes each chapter, in order, reading the
          previous chapter, the canon, the outline, and the continuity log.
          it updates a continuity log and a scene log as it goes.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>edit.</strong>
          focused editor passes &mdash; continuity, pacing, voice. these
          read the manuscript and revise where the agent itself catches
          drift. then a reader pass produces a letter on the finished book.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>publish.</strong>
          the press subsystem concatenates the drafts, builds the HTML / EPUB
          / PDF, synthesizes a cover brief from the canon via Claude, and
          generates the cover art and audiobook from there.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="prose reveal reveal-5">
      <h2>what isn&rsquo;t done</h2>
      <p>
        no human edits the prose. no human picks the cover image. the brief
        is the only thing a human writes. typos and infelicities are left in.
        an author&rsquo;s name does not appear on the books because there is
        no author in the sense the word usually carries.
      </p>
      <p>
        this is the point of the exercise. these books are not pretending to
        be written by anyone. they are demonstrations of what a particular
        kind of agent infrastructure can produce when set loose on a brief
        and allowed to finish.
      </p>
    </section>

    <Ornament variant="single" />

    <section class="prose reveal reveal-5">
      <h2>what the brief looks like</h2>
      <p>
        a brief is one to two pages of markdown. it names a premise, sketches
        the main characters, sets the period and place, fixes a target length,
        and lists a few hard constraints &mdash; what the book is not allowed
        to do, what it must honor, what the prose register must feel like.
        the more specific the brief, the more specific the result.
      </p>
      <p>
        if you would like to see one, every book on the shelf has its
        brief visible in the source repository, alongside the canon documents
        the agents wrote in response.
      </p>
      <p class="callout">
        the source code, the briefs, and every artifact is on
        <a href="https://github.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">github</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    padding-block: var(--space-5) var(--space-5);
  }

  .about-head {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 84, "SOFT" 65;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: -0.018em;
    margin-block: var(--space-2) var(--space-3);
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .about-title em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .lede {
    font-size: var(--size-lead);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }

  .prose {
    margin-block: var(--space-5);
  }

  .prose h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 42, "SOFT" 50;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 1.7rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .prose p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }

  .steps {
    list-style: none;
    counter-reset: step;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .steps li {
    counter-increment: step;
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 3.5rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }

  .steps li::before {
    content: counter(step, decimal-leading-zero);
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.15rem;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    color: var(--lantern);
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 24;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .steps strong {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 18;
  }

  .callout {
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
    padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3);
    background: rgba(201, 154, 74, 0.08);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--lantern);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }

  .callout a {
    color: var(--lantern-deep);
    border-bottom-color: var(--lantern-deep);
  }
</style>
